The paper focuses on using deep learning to predict the motion of a robotic agent from raw video frames, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed motion prediction network (PROM-Net) uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to learn visual representations of the environment, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The network is trained in an unsupervised manner, which involves learning from data without explicit labels, and this is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses using the predicted frames as input to a model predictive controller for motion planning, which involves decision-making and control in dynamic environments, and this is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
